{
  "analysis": "The current genseq still fails for non-empty inputs: /app/decomp outputs nothing, and decsim misdecodes token counts/tokens. Panel 1 correctly identifies a concrete put_integer bug: after the unary stop bit, the decoder reads exactly tmp binary bits, but the current code emits n-2 bits, which is wrong unless n==tmp+1. We also already fixed normalization bytes to emit low_byte+1 because the decoder adds gc()-1. The next step is to apply exactly that put_integer fix and re-test small cases through the real /app/decomp and decsim.",
  "plan": "Rewrite /app/genseq.c with put_integer emitting unary_length=n-tmp-1 zeros, one stop 1, then exactly tmp binary bits MSB-first from ans excluding the implicit leading 1. Keep normalization emitting ((low>>24)&0xff)+1. Compile and test 0 tokens, one literal 1, two literals 1 and 2, and match offset 1 length 1. Use /app/decomp and decsim diagnostics to verify behavior.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/genseq.c <<'C'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
static long low=0, range=1;
static int cc[2*200000];
static int radix=255;
static void norm(void){
  while(range<radix){
    putchar(((low>>24)&0xff)+1);
    low=(low&0xffffff)*radix;
    range*=radix;
  }
}
static void put_bit(int bit,int ctx){
  int *c=cc+ctx*2;
  long split=range*(c[0]+1)/(c[0]+c[1]+2);
  if(bit){ low+=split; range-=split; c[1]++; }
  else { range=split; c[0]++; }
  norm();
}
static void put_integer(int value,int tmp,int ctx){
  int ans=value+(1<<tmp), bits[64], n=0, t=ans;
  int i;
  while(t>0){bits[n++]=t&1;t>>=1;}
  int unary=n-tmp-1;
  ctx*=99;
  for(i=0;i<unary;i++) put_bit(0,tmp+1+i+ctx);
  put_bit(1,tmp+1+unary+ctx);
  for(i=tmp-1;i>=0;i--) put_bit((ans>>(i))&1,ctx);
}
static void finish(void){ while(range<radix){ putchar(((low>>24)&0xff)+1); low=(low&0xffffff)*radix; range*=radix; } }
static void lit(int v){ int sign=(v<0)?1:0; put_bit(0,1); put_bit(sign,8); put_integer(abs(v),4,9); }
static void match(int off,int len){ put_bit(1,1); put_integer(off-1,5,2); put_integer(len-1,2,3); }
int main(int argc,char**argv){
  int n=atoi(argv[1]);
  int i;
  put_integer(n,9,0);
  for(i=2;i<argc;i++){
    if(argv[i][0]=='m' && (i+2<argc)){ match(atoi(argv[i+1]),atoi(argv[i+2])); i+=2; }
    else { lit(atoi(argv[i])); }
  }
  finish();
  return 0;
}
